news.title: Supreme Court greenlights razing of 17 illegal buildings on private land in Thane
news.para: A partial working day bench of Justices Ujjal Bhuyan and Manmohan refused to stay the demolition order, pursuant to which Thane MC had demolished 8 buildings, on a plea by one Danish Zaheer Siddiqui, who claimed he had purchased a flat in those buildings.

news.title: Ahmedabad: AUDA approves hike in development fee for new projects
news.para: The proposal got the nod at its board meeting on Tuesday, paving the way for a 10-20-fold increase in the charges, which will directly impact the cost of residential, commercial, and other properties.

news.title: Blackstone’s Knowledge Realty Trust raises ₹1,400 crore in India's maiden REIT pre-IPO round
news.para: Knowledge Realty Trust (KRT), backed by Blackstone and Sattva Developers, raised ₹1,400 crore in a landmark pre-IPO placement. This marks India’s first such REIT fundraising, with participation from HNIs and family offices ahead of its ₹6,200 crore IPO.

news.title: Ahead of IPO, ArisInfra Solutions garners ₹225 crore from anchor investors
news.para: The nearly Rs 500-crore IPO will open for subscription on June 18 and conclude on June 20. The price band has been set at Rs 210 to Rs 222 per share for the public issue.

news.title: Delhi government considers mandatory water bill for property registration
news.para: According to sources, the government is considering Delhi Jal Board (DJB) reforms, and the water bill may become mandatory for property registration in Delhi.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves stamp duty concessions for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: An SPV has been established for the integrated redevelopment of Dharavi, one of the biggest slum sprawls in Asia which is located in central Mumbai.

news.title: Cement demand may be impacted in June due to early onset of monsoon: Ind-Ra
news.para: The cement volumes witnessed a "notable recovery of 10-11 per cent y-o-y" in the March 2025 quarter after recording a subdued 2 per cent growth in the first half of the last fiscal.

news.title: Homebuilder sentiment in USA skids to two and half years low in June: NAHB
news.para: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo Housing Market Index fell to 32, the lowest reading since December 2022, from 34 in May. Economists polled by Reuters had expected the sentiment score to improve to 36.

news.title: Sweden government plans to ease mortgage rules to help first-time buyers
news.para: Under the plan, people wanting a mortgage will be able to borrow up to 90% of the value of their property, up from the current 85%. A current requirement for the heaviest borrowers to pay back 3% of their loan each year will be dropped.

news.title: New World Development has paid dollar bond interest due Monday: Source
news.para: New World, which has one of the highest debt ratios among its peers and also changed its CEO twice last year, said earlier this month it would defer coupon payments worth $77.2 million on four perpetual bonds scheduled for June.

news.title: China's new homes demand to remain well short of 2017 peak: Goldman Sachs
news.para: China's property sector, which accounted for roughly a quarter of economic activity at its peak, entered a prolonged slump in 2021, with market sentiment hammered by the struggles of debt-laden developers trying to deliver homes for which buyers had already paid.

news.title: Blackstone acquires South City Mall in Kolkata for ₹3,250 crore
news.para: South City Mall was developed by South City Projects (Kolkata), a consortium of Merlin Group, Emami Group, Sachi Group, Surekha Group, JB Group and Rameswara Group and launched in January 2008.

news.title: StarBigBloc Building Material gets shareholder approval to launch IPO
news.para: StarBigBloc Building Material aims at increasing its production capacity from the current 250,000 cubic meters per annum to over 1.2 million cubic meters per annum over the next 4–5 years.

news.title: Environmental clearance now required for large township and construction projects in Chandigarh
news.para: Similarly, building and construction projects with more than 20,000 square metres and more than 1,50,000 square metres of built-up area will also need clearance. This is as per the latest notification issued by the UT department of environment.

news.title: About 3,200 street lights found non-functional in Patna
news.para: The survey was conducted in all the 75 wards of the city ahead of the monsoon season under the directive of the municipal commissioner. A total of 19 zonal officers were instructed to inspect the street lights in their respective areas.

news.title: To regularise illegal houses, Goa government plans bill to bypass comunidade
news.para: The govt, through the bill, will empower the administrator of the comunidade to decide on the application — bypassing the comunidade — to regularise the illegal structures on the respective comunidade, not exceeding an area of 300sqm.

news.title: Government to digitise land records of Goa’s urban areas
news.para: The initiative is expected to empower citizens, improve ease of living, enhance urban planning, and reduce land-related disputes.

news.title: About 35 property tax defaulters with ₹3.6 crore dues to get notices in Gurugram
news.para: In the current financial year (FY), the property tax revenue projection is pegged at Rs 275 crore, which is less than last FY's projection of Rs 300 crore. In 2024-25, MCG generated an income of Rs 232.9 crore, which was 77% of the projected estimate.

news.title: GDA seeks central funds for Noida-Ghaziabad metro link
news.para: GDA vice chairperson Atul Vats said on Monday, "We have written to UP govt. We have quoted a grant of Rs 2,441 crore, out of which Rs 1,873 crore is for the metro project."

news.title: Brick kilns, which employ thousands in Punjab, stare at closure
news.para: The number of brick kilns has reportedly come down from roughly about 2600 in 2021-22 to a little more than half, 1500, now.
